main event: Two UFO sightings reported in Wabash, Illinois on 21 June 1968, one at 3:40 AM and another at 4:30 AM.
interesting points: The observer claimed to have seen objects that looked like satellites, but the descriptions contained conflicting data; the sightings had varying reports of duration; the observer used binoculars for a closer view; the sightings were partially obscured by clouds; and the phenomenon reportedly changed brightness and colors during the observation.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects believed to be satellites
witness description: The witness described themselves as someone interested in UFOs, astronomy, and aeronautics.
